  "text": "Numerous Pontin and Reptin interaction partners have known roles in cancer. The first hints suggesting a relationship between Pontin, Reptin and cancer came with the discovery that both proteins interacted with ß-catenin [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and c-myc [CITATION_3] . Moreover, expression of both proteins is regulated by c-myc [CITATION_4] . Pontin appears to be required for the transforming effect of",
